fields.June 16)\":
For all the challenges:

1. The random pairing removed the benefit of getting to know with whom I work efficiently from my shortlist. Most of the time, I was paired with people I knew I don't click with.
2. The limited time frame (2h) meant we could spend max 20-30 min on ideation. This meant all the ideas were shallow and more for the sake of the challenge. If there was more time, 3-4h, that would give time to develop an idea that we would be enthusiastic about.
fields.\"Google Labs Event (Wed: For technical people, it was very shallow, for non-technical, it was too deep. I believe it would be more useful to focus on principles, e.g. advantages of serverless, than specific products
fields.Google Labs: Pros/Cons - Learnings/Criti: This was great level of detail, and I wish it was longer
fields.\"Masterclass 2: Sales & GTM - Matthieu: Presentation in French (I'm not a speaker), limited value
fields.June 17)\": The personal pitches on Monday came too late, it was at the moment when I already talked to most of people. If personal pitches would happen Friday morning / Thursday afternoon, they would be much more useful, to quickly understand the background and projects people want to work on.
